527
00:24:28,712 --> 00:24:33,395
So he called me and I drove up there.

528
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:38,733
I found her.

529
00:24:38,801 --> 00:24:42,504
She was just lying there.

530
00:24:45,041 --> 00:24:46,387
And then what?

531
00:24:46,387 --> 00:24:48,956
You cleaned up the flowers and candles

532
00:24:48,956 --> 00:24:50,879
so I wouldn't find out about mom and Ray?

533
00:24:50,947 --> 00:24:52,440
Whoa, what candles and flowers?

534
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,390
Dad, come on.

535
00:24:53,390 --> 00:24:54,864
Maybe you were trying to protect her reputation.

536
00:24:54,864 --> 00:24:56,318
What the hell are you talking about?

537
00:24:56,385 --> 00:24:58,320
Melinda, she had a vision. And in the vision...

538
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:00,445
You mean about the night your mother died?

539
00:25:00,445 --> 00:25:03,067
Ok, you two, enough.

540
00:25:03,859 --> 00:25:05,093
Evelyn?

541
00:25:05,161 --> 00:25:07,578
Well, you are a sight for dead eyes.

542
00:25:07,578 --> 00:25:08,872
Where have you been?

543
00:25:08,872 --> 00:25:10,314
Mom? It's really you?

544
00:25:10,333 --> 00:25:11,967
It's me.

545
00:25:12,035 --> 00:25:14,470
I'm so sorry to barge in on you like this,

546
00:25:14,537 --> 00:25:16,639
But really, what's the point of dredging all this up?

547
00:25:16,706 --> 00:25:17,740
It was so long ago.

548
00:25:17,807 --> 00:25:20,643
What's all this about candles and flowers?

549
00:25:20,710 --> 00:25:22,111
At my funeral? How nice.

550
00:25:22,178 --> 00:25:23,412
Got to go.

551
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:24,813
No, you stay put.

552
00:25:24,881 --> 00:25:26,849
Wait a minute.

553
00:25:26,916 --> 00:25:29,158
Candles and flowers.

554
00:25:29,610 --> 00:25:32,800
It was just like the first time that I caught you two up there.

555
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:33,922
Please, I'm begging you.

556
00:25:33,990 --> 00:25:36,258
Don and Anne got over it. We should, too.

557
00:25:36,326 --> 00:25:37,393
Anne knew about it?

558
00:25:37,460 --> 00:25:38,748
None of it was easy.

559
00:25:38,748 --> 00:25:41,196
That snake was with you the night you died?

560
00:25:41,264 --> 00:25:42,431
And you're still protecting him?

561
00:25:42,499 --> 00:25:43,799
Honestly, it isn't like that.

562
00:25:43,867 --> 00:25:45,234
What is it like then?

563
00:25:45,301 --> 00:25:47,469
We'll talk when you calm down.

564
00:25:47,537 --> 00:25:48,871
Evelyn!

565
00:25:48,938 --> 00:25:49,905
You come back here!

566
00:25:49,973 --> 00:25:51,373
Stop fighting!

567
00:25:51,441 --> 00:25:52,374
I'm sure it was just...

568
00:25:52,442 --> 00:25:53,375
No, no, no.

569
00:25:53,443 --> 00:25:54,443
You're still hanging around, huh,

570
00:25:54,511 --> 00:25:56,245
just waiting for him.

571
00:25:56,830 --> 00:25:59,982
The man who left you for dead on the bathroom floor.

572
00:26:01,351 --> 00:26:02,818
Fine.

573
00:26:03,876 --> 00:26:06,553
You want your precious Don?

574
00:26:07,657 --> 00:26:10,092
I'll bring him to you.

575
00:26:12,796 --> 00:26:13,962
Dad.

576
00:26:14,030 --> 00:26:15,764
Wait!

577
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:31,847
Anne?

578
00:27:20,997 --> 00:27:24,099
Please forgive me.

579
00:27:24,167 --> 00:27:25,868
I never meant to hurt you.

580
00:27:35,036 --> 00:27:37,899
My dad was shocked to find out the affair was still going on.

581
00:27:37,962 --> 00:27:39,507
So he wasn't the one who cleaned up.

582
00:27:39,507 --> 00:27:41,184
Ok, so we're back to Don.

583
00:27:41,184 --> 00:27:42,127
Here me out.

584
00:27:42,127 --> 00:27:44,715
It couldn't have been Mrs. Pilnick who called the caretaker.

585
00:27:44,715 --> 00:27:46,041
Who's Mrs. Pilnick?

586
00:27:46,041 --> 00:27:47,279
The lake busybody.

587
00:27:47,279 --> 00:27:50,900
Dad said that she had called the caretaker

588
00:27:50,900 --> 00:27:52,272
who called him the night mom died.

589
00:27:52,340 --> 00:27:53,573
But that was in November.

590
00:27:53,641 --> 00:27:56,362
And Mrs. Pilnick spent the winters in Boca.

591
00:27:56,362 --> 00:27:59,346
So somebody must have pretended to be her on the phone.

592
00:27:59,414 --> 00:28:01,214
A woman.

593
00:28:01,282 --> 00:28:03,250
Wait a minute..

594
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:05,218
There's a blonde in Aiden's drawing.

595
00:28:05,286 --> 00:28:06,720
It's Anne.

596
00:28:06,788 --> 00:28:08,455
Mom said she knew.

597
00:28:09,196 --> 00:28:11,406
Ok, well, did she know that they started up again?

598
00:28:11,406 --> 00:28:12,478
Makes sense.

599
00:28:12,478 --> 00:28:14,327
She could have went up there to confront mom.

600
00:28:14,395 --> 00:28:16,278
So they fought, there was a struggle,

601
00:28:16,278 --> 00:28:18,732
And that brought on the aneurysm.

602
00:28:22,236 --> 00:28:24,571
I don't think my dad got that update.

603
00:28:24,638 --> 00:28:26,339
What? What is it?

604
00:28:26,407 --> 00:28:27,908
Looks like he might have hurt Don.

605
00:28:27,908 --> 00:28:30,543
- There's blood and....  - Blood?

606
00:28:30,611 --> 00:28:32,191
Yeah.

607
00:28:32,191 --> 00:28:34,224
Strawberry.

608
00:28:34,224 --> 00:28:35,882
It's jam.

609
00:28:37,418 --> 00:28:39,035
Somebody's here. I gotta go.

610
00:28:39,035 --> 00:28:40,687
Wait...

611
00:28:43,290 --> 00:28:45,024
Eli, what are you doing here?

612
00:28:45,092 --> 00:28:47,209
Oh, uh, just looking for your parents. They're not here.

613
00:28:47,209 --> 00:28:48,432
Are you sure? Let me just...

614
00:28:48,432 --> 00:28:50,630
Positive. Yeah.

615
00:28:50,698 --> 00:28:53,215
Well, they didn't answer their phones, either,

616
00:28:53,215 --> 00:28:54,263
Which is typical.

617
00:28:54,263 --> 00:28:56,870
They must have gone out for breakfast before the funeral.

618
00:28:56,937 --> 00:28:58,905
Hopefully not a place with knives.

619
00:28:58,973 --> 00:29:00,240
What?

620
00:29:00,307 --> 00:29:03,576
Eli, what...why are you acting so weird?

621
00:29:03,644 --> 00:29:07,914
Sorry, I just have to give a eulogy

622
00:29:07,982 --> 00:29:10,083
that I haven't written yet.

623
00:29:10,394 --> 00:29:12,087
Yeah, I thought you wanted my help with that.

624
00:29:12,087 --> 00:29:15,201
You know, I've been calling and texting you.

625
00:29:15,201 --> 00:29:17,090
Did I do something wrong?

626
00:29:17,100 --> 00:29:19,034
No, of course not. No, no.

627
00:29:19,102 --> 00:29:21,770
God, I'm...I'm such a ditz.

628
00:29:21,838 --> 00:29:23,806
Here you are going through something so major

629
00:29:23,873 --> 00:29:26,208
and I'm being all selfish and making it about me.

630
00:29:26,276 --> 00:29:27,509
Sorry.

631
00:29:27,577 --> 00:29:30,512
I must have misread you the other day, that's all.

632
00:29:30,580 --> 00:29:33,729
And besides, we have too much history. Right?

633
00:29:33,729 --> 00:29:36,018
I mean, we're practically brother and sister, so.

634
00:29:36,086 --> 00:29:37,820
Yeah, no.

635
00:29:37,887 --> 00:29:41,156
Trust me, I'm really not trying to think of you that way.

636
00:29:41,224 --> 00:29:43,959
Um, anyway, we're late. We should go.

637
00:29:44,027 --> 00:29:45,194
I'll drive. Let's...

638
00:29:55,739 --> 00:29:57,739
Ah, it's his voicemail again. Where is he?

639
00:29:57,740 --> 00:29:59,174
Maybe he found his parents again.

640
00:29:59,241 --> 00:30:00,341
Hopefully Casey's.

641
00:30:00,409 --> 00:30:01,951
I guess Ray did something drastic.

642
00:30:01,951 --> 00:30:04,273
I checked all the emergency rooms and the local hospitals.

643
00:30:04,273 --> 00:30:05,640
Neither parent were admitted.

644
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:07,649
Did you check the morgues?

645
00:30:07,716 --> 00:30:09,823
Ooh, finally.

646
00:30:11,620 --> 00:30:13,488
- Are they here?  - Who, my parents?

647
00:30:14,517 --> 00:30:16,124
Yeah.

648
00:30:16,192 --> 00:30:17,692
Uh, I haven't... I haven't seen them yet.

649
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:18,793
Any of them.

650
00:30:18,861 --> 00:30:20,929
Ok, now I'm worried.

651
00:30:20,996 --> 00:30:22,363
You and me both.

652
00:30:22,431 --> 00:30:24,999
We come here today to honor Raymond James

653
00:30:25,067 --> 00:30:29,420
as he joins his wife Evelyn in eternal peace.

654
00:30:29,420 --> 00:30:30,772
We should be so lucky.

655
00:30:30,840 --> 00:30:35,378
Their beloved son Eli has asked to say a few words.

656
00:30:35,378 --> 00:30:36,852
Eli?

657
00:30:49,374 --> 00:30:52,327
What can I say about my dad?

658
00:30:52,767 --> 00:30:57,555
Except that he was larger than life.

659
00:30:57,867 --> 00:30:59,677
Especially when it came to

660
00:30:59,678 --> 00:31:03,902
the way he loved my mom.

661
00:31:09,644 --> 00:31:13,072
You all know my dad was a little crazy.

662
00:31:13,749 --> 00:31:15,783
Love can do that to a person sometimes.

663
00:31:15,851 --> 00:31:20,788
It can make a person do really stupid things.

664
00:31:20,856 --> 00:31:22,991
But love can be a pain, too,

665
00:31:23,058 --> 00:31:27,806
Because, you know, we can't choose we fall in love with.

666
00:31:29,298 --> 00:31:30,999
The heart just goes where it goes

667
00:31:31,066 --> 00:31:34,602
and it's not always a recipe for happiness.

668
00:31:34,670 --> 00:31:38,717
You've got a hell of a nerve showing your sorry face at my funeral.

669
00:31:45,881 --> 00:31:46,981
My god.

670
00:31:48,184 --> 00:31:49,444
I'm overcome.

671
00:31:49,444 --> 00:31:51,425
- Dad.  - Don, are you ok?

672
00:31:51,425 --> 00:31:53,532
You tell him I'm just getting warmed up.

673
00:31:53,532 --> 00:31:55,390
Stop it!

674
00:31:57,693 --> 00:31:59,727
Jim, could you just stall?

675
00:31:59,795 --> 00:32:01,663
Yeah.

676
00:32:02,505 --> 00:32:04,098
You guys, follow me.

677
00:32:05,134 --> 00:32:07,035
We'll be right back.

678
00:32:07,102 --> 00:32:08,336
Thank you.

679
00:32:08,404 --> 00:32:10,205
Let's go.

680
00:32:10,272 --> 00:32:12,530
Ok, so I didn't believe you about all this ghost stuff,

681
00:32:12,530 --> 00:32:15,677
But I swear, Ray's been trying to kill me all morning.

682
00:32:15,744 --> 00:32:19,414
A ghost? Dad, what's going on?

683
00:32:19,481 --> 00:32:21,249
Make it stop, please.

684
00:32:21,317 --> 00:32:22,584
You can do that, right?

685
00:32:22,651 --> 00:32:24,285
I can try. I mean, Ray is with us.

686
00:32:24,353 --> 00:32:25,462
What?

687
00:32:25,462 --> 00:32:29,257
Casey, look, Melinda can see ghosts and I can hear them.

688
00:32:29,325 --> 00:32:30,758
And I know this sounds crazy,

689
00:32:30,826 --> 00:32:32,694
but my parents are stuck here

690
00:32:32,761 --> 00:32:35,165
because you and I might be related.

691
00:32:35,165 --> 00:32:37,232
Is Evelyn here, too?

692
00:32:37,299 --> 00:32:39,133
She is now.

693
00:32:39,201 --> 00:32:40,902
Well, it's about damn time.

694
00:32:40,970 --> 00:32:42,203
I haven't been losing my mind.

695
00:32:42,271 --> 00:32:45,100
She really has been haunting me all these years.

696
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:47,008
Yeah, because you left her for dead.

697
00:32:47,076 --> 00:32:48,676
Or maybe you even caused her death

698
00:32:48,744 --> 00:32:50,378
when you confronted her about the affair.

699
00:32:50,446 --> 00:32:52,247
No, no. Eli, stop it, please.

700
00:32:52,314 --> 00:32:53,314
You have it all wrong.

701
00:32:53,382 --> 00:32:54,812
Affair?

702
00:32:54,940 --> 00:32:57,285
Will somebody please tell me what's going on?

703
00:32:57,285 --> 00:32:58,987
I told you to leave it alone.

704
00:32:59,054 --> 00:33:00,822
You see the mess you've made.

705
00:33:00,889 --> 00:33:02,189
You don't even deny it, do you?

706
00:33:02,189 --> 00:33:03,295
How could you do that?

707
00:33:03,295 --> 00:33:05,426
Leave her alone. She didn't do anything.

708
00:33:05,494 --> 00:33:08,596
- She hurt you, mom.  - No! She was...

709
00:33:08,664 --> 00:33:10,505
Protecting me.

710
00:33:10,505 --> 00:33:13,234
Protecting you from what?

711
00:33:15,834 --> 00:33:17,205
Ray.

712
00:33:17,273 --> 00:33:18,806
What?

713
00:33:18,874 --> 00:33:21,509
I was unfaithful.

714
00:33:21,577 --> 00:33:24,078
But not with Don.

715
00:33:26,548 --> 00:33:27,715
Evelyn.

716
00:33:27,783 --> 00:33:29,817
What are they saying?

717
00:33:31,053 --> 00:33:32,920
Evelyn's confessing.

718
00:33:32,988 --> 00:33:36,324
She was unfaithful, but not with Don.

719
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:39,761
She's telling the truth.

720
00:33:41,430 --> 00:33:43,865
I was protecting her.

721
00:33:43,932 --> 00:33:46,434
Because she did have an affair.

722
00:33:49,305 --> 00:33:51,439
With me.

723
00:34:05,258 --> 00:34:07,193
Evelyn.

724
00:34:08,395 --> 00:34:09,762
What the hell is...

725
00:34:09,830 --> 00:34:13,299
I'm so sorry you had to find out like this.

726
00:34:13,367 --> 00:34:16,335
I lived a lifetime of guilt and shame.

727
00:34:16,403 --> 00:34:18,371
Death gave me perspective.

728
00:34:18,439 --> 00:34:22,108
My only regret is that I deceived you.

729
00:34:22,176 --> 00:34:26,530
-I couldn't love you the way you deserved.  -No, no. That's not possible.

730
00:34:26,530 --> 00:34:30,516
Now, look, I caught you and Don red-handed. I mean...

731
00:34:30,584 --> 00:34:33,691
No, but I just let you think you did.

732
00:34:33,691 --> 00:34:37,346
Evelyn wanted Ray to think that the affair was with Don.

733
00:34:37,826 --> 00:34:41,719
Mom, is this real?

734
00:34:41,787 --> 00:34:44,122
It is, sweetie.

735
00:34:44,977 --> 00:34:46,524
Years ago, Evelyn and I...

736
00:34:47,542 --> 00:34:50,884
We'd go up to the lake house to open it up for the summer.

737
00:34:52,698 --> 00:34:55,288
One thing led to another and

738
00:34:55,978 --> 00:34:57,168
we fell in love.

739
00:34:57,236 --> 00:34:59,704
And that's where you went to be together?

740
00:35:01,107 --> 00:35:02,607
The night Evvy gave me that necklace,

741
00:35:02,675 --> 00:35:04,676
Ray showed up.

742
00:35:04,743 --> 00:35:07,946
I'm sorry, Don. I'm stuck at the shop a few more hours.

743
00:35:08,761 --> 00:35:11,082
There's lasagna in the freezer.

744
00:35:11,082 --> 00:35:12,587
Bye.

745
00:35:14,890 --> 00:35:16,421
Ray!

746
00:35:16,422 --> 00:35:19,780
It was Ray coming up the steps whistling.

747
00:35:26,013 --> 00:35:27,432
Ray?

748
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:29,258
Evvy?

749
00:35:43,782 --> 00:35:46,417
It all happened so fast.

750
00:35:46,485 --> 00:35:47,986
I saw Ray in my rearview mirror.

751
00:35:49,355 --> 00:35:52,223
And all I saw...

752
00:35:52,291 --> 00:35:54,718
All I saw then was Don's car.

753
00:35:54,718 --> 00:35:57,195
Anne was driving Don's car.

754
00:35:57,263 --> 00:35:58,696
That's why he thought it was him.

755
00:35:58,764 --> 00:36:00,298
And I let him think that.

756
00:36:00,366 --> 00:36:02,867
I could barely handle the truth myself.

757
00:36:02,935 --> 00:36:04,334
How could I expect you to?

758
00:36:04,334 --> 00:36:06,838
Yeah, but look, Don never denied it.

759
00:36:06,906 --> 00:36:09,841
I mean, why the hell would he even go along with it?

760
00:36:09,909 --> 00:36:14,479
Don, my father wants to know why you let him believe it was you.

761
00:36:16,882 --> 00:36:19,951
It's because you knew, didn't you?

762
00:36:21,086 --> 00:36:22,837
I suspected.

763
00:36:23,283 --> 00:36:24,756
And when Ray accused me,

764
00:36:24,823 --> 00:36:27,392
It just all sort of made sense.

765
00:36:30,029 --> 00:36:32,163
But my family was important then.

766
00:36:32,231 --> 00:36:34,377
And they are now.

767
00:36:36,569 --> 00:36:38,169
I didn't want to lose you.

768
00:36:39,196 --> 00:36:40,505
I felt the same.

769
00:36:41,941 --> 00:36:43,474
So when Evvy died,

770
00:36:43,542 --> 00:36:45,944
I let our secret die with her.

771
00:36:46,011 --> 00:36:47,712
I didn't want to hurt anyone.

772
00:36:48,914 --> 00:36:50,014
Neither did I, Ray.

773
00:36:50,779 --> 00:36:52,875
Especially after the way you reacted.

774
00:36:53,519 --> 00:36:56,688
I'd never seen you so angry.

775
00:36:56,755 --> 00:36:58,957
And even worse, so hurt.

776
00:37:01,827 --> 00:37:03,995
How do you think I feel now?

777
00:37:05,898 --> 00:37:08,539
You were there the night Evelyn died.

778
00:37:09,159 --> 00:37:11,936
A few days before I'd broken it off again.

779
00:37:12,004 --> 00:37:13,805
Gave her back the necklace.

780
00:37:13,872 --> 00:37:16,341
But then she called me from the lake house

781
00:37:16,408 --> 00:37:17,342
And I drove up to see her.

782
00:37:17,409 --> 00:37:18,824
I knew I shouldn't.

783
00:37:18,824 --> 00:37:20,511
The thing is,

784
00:37:20,579 --> 00:37:23,781
I died hours before she got there.

785
00:37:31,724 --> 00:37:34,225
I hit my head on the sink when I fell.

786
00:37:34,293 --> 00:37:35,226
Evvy!

787
00:37:35,294 --> 00:37:36,661
Just like the coroner said.

788
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:43,735
Evvy.

789
00:37:43,802 --> 00:37:46,537
She didn't have a pulse.

790
00:37:46,605 --> 00:37:47,739
Her skin was so cold.

791
00:37:47,806 --> 00:37:49,007
Evvy! Oh, my god.

792
00:37:49,074 --> 00:37:50,341
- She was dead. - No!

793
00:37:50,409 --> 00:37:51,876
I didn't know what had happened.

794
00:37:51,944 --> 00:37:53,978
I knew that if anybody found her like that,

795
00:37:54,046 --> 00:37:55,647
with the candles and the flowers...

796
00:37:55,714 --> 00:37:59,250
I panicked. I hid everything.

797
00:38:06,925 --> 00:38:09,394
I hated leaving you like that, Evvy.

798
00:38:09,461 --> 00:38:12,163
I just didn't know what else to do.

799
00:38:13,532 --> 00:38:16,100
Please tell her I'd have done the same thing.

800
00:38:16,168 --> 00:38:17,402
I was dead.

801
00:38:17,469 --> 00:38:20,305
Why put our families through anymore pain?

802
00:38:20,372 --> 00:38:22,106
She understands

803
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:23,808
why you did that.

804
00:38:23,876 --> 00:38:27,445
No wonder you were so upset when she died.

805
00:38:27,513 --> 00:38:31,416
I thought I was protecting her.

806
00:38:31,483 --> 00:38:34,619
Ray and Eli and you, Casey, and Don.

807
00:38:35,383 --> 00:38:38,423
I carry that guilt with me every day since.

808
00:38:38,490 --> 00:38:40,425
But you called the caretaker

809
00:38:40,492 --> 00:38:42,060
so that somebody would find her.

810
00:38:42,127 --> 00:38:46,230
I couldn't bear the thought of her just lying there dead like that.

811
00:38:46,979 --> 00:38:51,135
So our marriage was just some lie?

812
00:38:52,237 --> 00:38:53,905
It's not that simple.

813
00:38:53,972 --> 00:38:55,773
I just...

814
00:38:55,841 --> 00:38:58,409
I couldn't change who I am.

815
00:38:59,511 --> 00:39:01,179
What is it? What are they saying?

816
00:39:02,581 --> 00:39:05,149
They have some stuff to figure out.

817
00:39:07,152 --> 00:39:08,519
So do we.

818
00:39:10,789 --> 00:39:13,091
Let's go home.

819
00:39:20,265 --> 00:39:22,233
I do love you, Ray.

820
00:39:22,301 --> 00:39:26,604
So much that I wanted you to be able to die in peace.

821
00:39:26,672 --> 00:39:28,172
And if there is another life waiting,

822
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:32,243
I hope to be honest with myself and the people I love.

823
00:39:32,311 --> 00:39:34,011
What you're saying is that

824
00:39:34,079 --> 00:39:38,149
you could only truly be happy if...

825
00:39:38,217 --> 00:39:40,862
if I would have just stepped aside?

826
00:39:40,862 --> 00:39:42,253
Not this time around.

827
00:39:42,321 --> 00:39:44,822
I wasn't strong enough for that.

828
00:39:44,890 --> 00:39:47,992
But Eli, you said it yourself,

829
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:51,628
the heart goes where it goes.

830
00:39:52,997 --> 00:39:54,869
This life is done now.

831
00:39:54,869 --> 00:39:57,461
But I just hope...

832
00:39:58,389 --> 00:40:01,203
Can you ever forgive me?

833
00:40:03,494 --> 00:40:07,196
Honestly, I... I don't know.

834
00:40:08,599 --> 00:40:13,536
But maybe...maybe you can help me get there.

835
00:40:15,506 --> 00:40:17,307
Maybe.

836
00:40:23,847 --> 00:40:25,315
Oh, my.

837
00:40:25,382 --> 00:40:28,818
It's so beautiful.

838
00:40:31,555 --> 00:40:34,651
Are you ready to say good-bye?

839
00:40:35,319 --> 00:40:37,226
I don't think I can.

840
00:40:38,101 --> 00:40:39,662
What is it, sweetie?

841
00:40:41,932 --> 00:40:44,067
I know that you two have to move on,

842
00:40:44,134 --> 00:40:47,570
and I know some day I'm gonna join you,

843
00:40:47,638 --> 00:40:49,174
But right now, after all this,

844
00:40:49,174 --> 00:40:52,241
I just feel like there's so much I don't know about you.

845
00:40:52,309 --> 00:40:53,843
Ray, maybe we should stay.

846
00:40:53,911 --> 00:40:54,877
What?

847
00:40:54,945 --> 00:40:56,717
Well, we can't leave him like this.

848
00:40:56,717 --> 00:40:57,981
Not right now.

849
00:40:58,048 --> 00:40:59,349
He's a grown man.

850
00:40:59,416 --> 00:41:02,267
Mom, don't just stay because of me. You shouldn't.

851
00:41:02,267 --> 00:41:04,053
What better reason would there be?

852
00:41:04,121 --> 00:41:06,122
Evelyn, we're gonna miss the bus.

853
00:41:06,190 --> 00:41:08,057
The light's fading. Come on.

854
00:41:08,125 --> 00:41:10,026
It'll be back.

855
00:41:10,094 --> 00:41:12,962
And so will we.

856
00:41:25,275 --> 00:41:28,494
I still just can't believe my mom was gay.

857
00:41:28,494 --> 00:41:30,446
You know, that might not have been the word she would have used.

858
00:41:30,514 --> 00:41:33,983
I've counseled so many patients in her situation.

859
00:41:34,051 --> 00:41:36,452
Maybe if she just would have told us.

860
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:37,754
It would have been hard,

861
00:41:37,821 --> 00:41:39,255
But we would have worked through it.

862
00:41:39,323 --> 00:41:40,490
You still will.

863
00:41:40,557 --> 00:41:42,392
And when they're ready, they'll move on.

864
00:41:42,459 --> 00:41:45,294
But hey, the good news is you and Casey can be together.

865
00:41:45,362 --> 00:41:47,363
She still hasn't called.

866
00:41:47,431 --> 00:41:49,465
We're supposed to get together later for a drink.

867
00:41:49,533 --> 00:41:51,934
You know, you might want to change.

868
00:41:52,002 --> 00:41:53,903
Why?

869
00:41:53,971 --> 00:41:57,507
I know what'll happen. We'll go out on a few dates, if I'm lucky.

870
00:41:57,574 --> 00:41:59,676
She'll tell me she's really starting to like me

871
00:41:59,743 --> 00:42:01,377
and she thinks what a unique guy I am,

872
00:42:01,445 --> 00:42:04,547
but the ghost thing freaks her out.

873
00:42:04,615 --> 00:42:06,282
Not if she's the right person.

874
00:42:06,350 --> 00:42:08,651
We'll see.

875
00:42:08,719 --> 00:42:10,153
Anyway, thanks.

876
00:42:13,590 --> 00:42:15,625
It's Casey. I should...

877
00:42:15,693 --> 00:42:18,594
Hey, Case.

878
00:42:18,662 --> 00:42:21,452
Yeah.

879
00:42:21,899 --> 00:42:24,934
Well, yeah. I like you, too.

880
00:42:25,002 --> 00:42:27,003
A lot. And I...

881
00:42:29,239 --> 00:42:31,374
Unique, huh?

882
00:42:33,143 --> 00:42:34,811
So I've been told.

